afterInput and beforeInput\par
With these properties you can add multiple components before and after the input element, as their name suggests. This is useful when you need to render additional elements alongside the field without replacing the entire field component.\par
\par
To add components before and after the input element, use the admin.components.beforeInput and admin.components.afterInput properties in your Field Config:\par
\par
import type \{ CollectionConfig \} from 'payload'\par
\par
export const MyCollectionConfig: CollectionConfig = \{\par
  // ...\par
  fields: [\par
    // ...\par
    \{\par
      name: 'myField',\par
      type: 'text',\par
      admin: \{\par
        components: \{\par
          beforeInput: ['/path/to/MyCustomComponent'],\par
          afterInput: ['/path/to/MyOtherCustomComponent'],\par
        \},\par
      \},\par
    \},\par
  ],\par
\}\par
All afterInput and beforeInput Components receive the same Default Field Component Props.\par
\par
For details on how to build Custom Components, see Building Custom Components.\par
\par
TypeScript\par
You can import the Payload Field type as well as other common types from the payload package. More details.\par
\par
import type \{ Field \} from 'payload'\f0\par
}
